# Wrangler asset-upload allowlist (gitignore syntax, read from the asset
# directory root — the repository root per wrangler.jsonc).
#
# STRATEGY: deny-by-default. Exclude every top-level entry, then re-include
# only the production web surface. Anything not explicitly re-included below
# (node_modules/, scripts/, .git/, PDFs, Python toolchain, caches, secrets)
# is shielded from cloud uploads by construction. This guards the 25 MiB
# per-asset Cloudflare limit that the original repo-root upload violated.

# 1. Exclude everything at the top level.
/*

# 2. Re-include the business landing page surface (site root).
!/index.html
!/reviews.html
!/style.css
!/favicon.ico
!/favicon.png
# Self-hosted font mirror (no trailing slash — same wrangler bare-path
# matching caveat as /ode below).
!/fonts

# 3. Re-include the ODE roadmap SPA, served under /ode/.
# (No trailing slash: wrangler tests bare path strings, so "/ode/" would
# fail to match the directory entry itself.)
!/ode

# 4. Credential hard-deny (belt and suspenders). Later rules win in
# gitignore syntax, so even if a future edit broadens the allowlist above,
# these files can never reach a Cloudflare upload.
token.json
client_secrets.json
client_secret*.json
credentials.json
*.pem
.env
.env.*

# 5. Development, source, and compilation hard-deny (belt and suspenders).
# The /* rule in §1 already excludes everything not re-included in §2/§3, so
# these are redundant BY DEFAULT. They exist so a future broadening of the
# allowlist can never leak raw curriculum data, the Python toolchain, LaTeX
# build sources, or editor/build caches into the asset upload. Because later
# rules win, the compilation patterns below ALSO re-exclude the LaTeX sources
# that sit UNDER the re-included /ode tree (ode/assets/markdowns/*.tex, ~117
# files, source-only and never fetched at runtime) — trimming edge weight
# while leaving the shipped cheat-sheet PDFs (ode/assets/pdfs/*.pdf) and the
# SPA data mirrors (ode/data/*.json) untouched.
#
# DELIBERATELY NOT LISTED: *.pdf and *.json. Both would win over the !/ode
# re-include and silently drop production assets — the 58 cheat-sheet PDFs
# and the curriculum/quiz JSON mirrors the SPA serves. Prune by directory or
# extension, never by those two globs.
scripts/
content/
src/
docs/
*.py
__pycache__/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
# LaTeX authoring + compilation fragments (curriculum print pipeline).
*.tex
*.aux
*.toc
*.out
*.fls
*.fdb_latexmk
*.synctex.gz
# Per-unit raw data fragments (frozen migration sources under scripts/).
unit*_data.json
